{"info": {"author": "Chijun Sima, Yixue Zhong", "author_email": "simachijun@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "description": "# nut_cloud\n\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/nut-cloud.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/nut-cloud)\n\nan online shop and a cloud drive using SQLite, Flask as the backend and the Bootstrap framework to ameliorate the appearance of the frontend.\n\n## Usage\n\n### The first time\n\n1. `pip install nut-cloud`\n2. + For Linux/macos/BSDs: `$ export FLASK_APP=\"nut_cloud\"`\n   + For Windows Powershell: `$ $env:FLASK_APP=\"nut_cloud\"`\n3. `$ flask init-db` (Only needed on the first time running nut_cloud)\n4. `$ flask run`\n\n### Later\n\n`$ python -c 'import nut_cloud; nut_cloud.create_app().run()'`\n\n## CAUTION\n\nYou need to configure the `SECRET_KEY`, `WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY` and the `HOSTNAME` yourself!\n\nYou can put a `config.py` in the app instance folder to configure these settings.\n\n## Auto deploy\n\nYou can configure your `WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY` to match the secret key of Github Webhooks, \nthen you can use Systemd to monitor file changes under `{instance path}/restart/` and \nrestart the `uwsgi` server each time any file is changed.\n\n## Language\n\nSimplified Chinese\n\n## License\n\nCopyright (c) 2018-2019 Chijun Sima, Yixue Zhong\n\nLicensed under the MIT License.\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/NutshellySima/nut_cloud", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "nut-cloud", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/nut-cloud/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/nut-cloud/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/NutshellySima/nut_cloud"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/nut-cloud/20.3.1/", "requires_dist": ["flask", "zxcvbn", "PyNaCl", "hurry.filesize", "qrcode", "click", "markdown2", "Pillow"], "requires_python": ">=3", "summary": "A website featuring a cloud drive and an online shop.", "version": "20.3.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>nut_cloud</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/nut-cloud\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PyPI version\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/931776a929162398ffd35a2cbc3dbdbf0f115168/68747470733a2f2f62616467652e667572792e696f2f70792f6e75742d636c6f75642e737667\"></a></p>\n<p>an online shop and a cloud drive using SQLite, Flask as the backend and the Bootstrap framework to ameliorate the appearance of the frontend.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<h3>The first time</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><code>pip install nut-cloud</code></li>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li>For Linux/macos/BSDs: <code>$ export FLASK_APP=\"nut_cloud\"</code></li>\n<li>For Windows Powershell: <code>$ $env:FLASK_APP=\"nut_cloud\"</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>$ flask init-db</code> (Only needed on the first time running nut_cloud)</li>\n<li><code>$ flask run</code></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Later</h3>\n<p><code>$ python -c 'import nut_cloud; nut_cloud.create_app().run()'</code></p>\n<h2>CAUTION</h2>\n<p>You need to configure the <code>SECRET_KEY</code>, <code>WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY</code> and the <code>HOSTNAME</code> yourself!</p>\n<p>You can put a <code>config.py</code> in the app instance folder to configure these settings.</p>\n<h2>Auto deploy</h2>\n<p>You can configure your <code>WEBHOOK_SECRET_KEY</code> to match the secret key of Github Webhooks,\nthen you can use Systemd to monitor file changes under <code>{instance path}/restart/</code> and\nrestart the <code>uwsgi</code> server each time any file is changed.</p>\n<h2>Language</h2>\n<p>Simplified Chinese</p>\n<h2>License</h2>\n<p>Copyright (c) 2018-2019 Chijun Sima, Yixue Zhong</p>\n<p>Licensed under the MIT License.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6728020, "releases": {"19.3.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "aed2601f33f5ac92fc7e5b6f9cc7aa48", "sha256": "4481c940afa95626ec7790b2903d4739f84ee90b015787be36b589956d070f32"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "nut_cloud-19.3.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "aed2601f33f5ac92fc7e5b6f9cc7aa48", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3", "size": 47884, "upload_time": "2019-03-02T15:35:23", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-03-02T15:35:23.959228Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/cf/a1/aced1455ed389dab69462672e07e89a743b55a0c97592169e172e4517692/nut_cloud-19.3.2-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "982f58cabc5f1e572cad28495128d366", "sha256": "d66dedf22aee2d972836237142eb5f03c66569ba4a7adbb19f2f76bb7487b3f5"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "nut_cloud-19.3.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "982f58cabc5f1e572cad28495128d366", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3", "size": 34192, "upload_time": "2019-03-02T15:35:25", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-03-02T15:35:25.950781Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f0/b7/4b6f1c6e6bf65618f438ca2edf7dd59e5f847e799313da35225008d6ecb9/nut_cloud-19.3.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "20.3.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "4d84ecb43f4b3786e0bbf529037e5ac9", "sha256": "3b57d8b5865998a9ccade74a355a9e02573f4f63581a709975ff9ccdefaa64f7"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "nut_cloud-20.3.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "4d84ecb43f4b3786e0bbf529037e5ac9", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3", "size": 389380, "upload_time": "2020-03-01T11:13:30", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-01T11:13:30.124551Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/c4/ac/c58240613659e5674e2e78ab43687256a1